31/05/2004
KARBALA, Iraq -- Bulgarian troops positioned at Karbala will be transferred within three months, according to reports Monday (31 May) quoting Bulgarian Chief of Staff General Nikola Kolev. Karbala has been the scene of heavy fighting since April. The troops would be moved to a Polish camp outside the city.
In other news, Bulgarian Parliament Speaker Ognyan Gerdjikov said on Sunday that he would not call for a parliamentary declaration urging a change in the verdict handed down against several Bulgarian nurses in Libya, despite enormous pressure to do so. Gerdjikov says "silent diplomacy" is the only feasible approach. (Sega - 31/05/04; Bulgarian National Radio - 30/05/04)
